  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Post thyroidectomy laryngeal nerve injuries are frequently encountered specially in total and
      near total thyroidectomy some unilateral injuries are not clinically evident and
      asymptomatic.

      The aim of this study is to compare mandatory versus selective post-thyroidectomy endoscopic
      examination of larynx to detect laryngeal nerve injuries.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      100 patients were randomly divided into two groups, group I for whom mandatory post
      thyroidectomy endoscopic laryngoscopic examination and the other group of only symptomatic
      patients selected for direct laryngoscopic examination.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
